Whisk together vinaigrette ingredients. Blanch and peel tomatoes . Seed and cut into 1-inch pieces. Wrap shallots in a kitchen towel, then twist and squeeze to remove as much liquid as possible. Cook broccoli, cauliflower, celery root, turnips, and haricots verts in a large pot of boiling salted water until crisp-tender, about 5 minutes, then drain well. Toss warm vegetables with tomatoes, shallots, chives, cilantro, and vinaigrette.